Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
queryDensityInBox(25.10)                              queryDensityInBox(25.10)

Name
       queryDensityInBox  -  Outputs  placement density for a specific area in
       the design

Syntax
       queryDensityInBox

       <query_box>

       Outputs placement density for a specific area in the design.  Considers
       placement  blockages  and honors the metal layers specified by the set-
       PlaceMode -place_detail_preroute_as_obs. The argument type  is  box  in
       units  of microns. This command is optimized for small area interactive
       queries.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each queryDensityInBox parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man queryDensityInBox

       <query_box>
              Specifies box coordinates (<x1>, <y1>, <x2>, <y2>) in micron.

              * x1: Specifies the area's lower left point on the x axis.

              * y1: Specifies the area's lower left point on the y axis.

              * x2: Specifies the area's upper right point on the x axis.

              * y2: Specifies the area's upper right point on the y axis.

Example
       The  following  command  reports the placement density for the specific
       area 2835.342 3381.807 4807.673 4530.904:

       queryDensityInBox 2835.342 3381.807 4807.673 4530.904

       The output of this command is:

       StdInstArea/freeSpace = 27.0%(197105.76/728824.32)

       macroInstArea/totArea = 67.7%(1539687.84/2272665.60)

       powerMetalArea/totArea = 0.0%(0.00/2272665.60)

       PlacementObsArea/totArea = 0.0%(0.00/2272665.60)

       Utilization in area (2835342 3381807) (4807673 4530904) = 27.04%

